{
  "title": "Variables and Basic Data Types",
  "description": "",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "What Is a Variable?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A variable is a name used to store a value in memory. You can think of a variable as a labeled box where you decide what to put inside."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For example:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "name = \"Python\"\nage = 33"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Here:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "The \"label\" is <code class=\"language-python\">name</code> or <code class=\"language-python\">age</code>.",
        "The content is <code class=\"language-python\">\"Python\"</code> and <code class=\"language-python\">33</code>."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "üìå <strong>Note:</strong><br>The <code class=\"language-python\">=</code> sign in Python does not mean \"mathematically equal\", but \"assign a value\". In other words: \"store this value in this variable\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Python and Dynamic Typing"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Python determines the variable type automatically based on the value you assign to it."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "x = 10       # int (integer)\nx = \"Hello\"   # str (string)"
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "‚≠ê <strong>Tip:</strong><br>You can change the type at any time, but avoid doing so. Keeping a consistent type makes your code clearer."
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Rules For Naming Variables"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Python allows many valid names, but you must follow these rules:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "You can only use letters, numbers and underscores.",
        "It cannot start with a number.",
        "Do not use spaces.",
        "Avoid reserved words (<code class=\"language-python\">for</code>, <code class=\"language-python\">if</code>, <code class=\"language-python\">print</code>, etc.)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Valid examples:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "user_name = \"Ana\"\nage2 = 30\n_total = 99"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Invalid examples:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "2age = 10\nmy variable = \"text\"\nfor = 5"
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "üìå <strong>Note:</strong><br>Use descriptive names. Your code will be easier to read without needing comments."
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Basic Data Types in Python"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Let‚Äôs look at the most common types to start with:"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "1. Integers - <code class=\"language-python\">int</code>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Numbers without decimals."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "age = 20\nyear = 2025"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "2. Floats - <code class=\"language-python\">float</code>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Numbers with decimals."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "price = 19.99\ntemperature = 36.5"
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "‚≠ê <strong>Tip:</strong><br>Floats can behave strangely because of how they are represented internally:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "print(0.1 + 0.2)\n# 0.30000000000000004"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "But don‚Äôt worry, you‚Äôll learn more about this later."
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "3. Strings - <code class=\"language-python\">str</code>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Any text inside single or double quotes."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "name = \"Python\"\nmessage = 'Hello world'"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You can use triple quotes for long text:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "long_text = \"\"\"This is a text\nthat spans multiple lines\"\"\""
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "4. Booleans - <code class=\"language-python\">bool</code>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Represent true or false:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "active = True\nlogged_in = False"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "They are used very often in conditionals."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "üìå <strong>Note:</strong><br>In Python, <code class=\"language-python\">True</code> and <code class=\"language-python\">False</code> start with uppercase letters."
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Check The Type Of a Variable"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You can use the <code class=\"language-python\">type()</code> function to check the datatype:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "x = 10\nprint(type(x))   # &lt;class 'int'&gt;"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "x = 10\nprint(type(x))"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This is very useful when you are learning."
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Operations By Data Type"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Each type has specific operations:"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "Integers and Floats"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "a = 10\nb = 2.5\nresult = a + b   # 12.5"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "Strings"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Concatenation:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "greeting = \"Hello\" + \" \" + \"World\"\nprint(greeting)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Output:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "Hello World"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "greeting = \"Hello\" + \" \" + \"World\"\nprint(greeting)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Repetition:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "print(\"Hello\" * 3)\n# HelloHelloHello"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "print(\"Hello\" * 3)"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "Booleans"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "true_val = True\nfalse_val = False\nprint(true_val and false_val)  # False"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "true_val = True\nfalse_val = False\nprint(true_val and false_val)  # False"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Type Conversion (Casting)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Python allows converting values manually:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "age = \"20\"\nage = int(age)\nprint(type(age))    # &lt;class 'int'&gt;"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "age = \"20\"\nage = int(age)\nprint(type(age))"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Or from number to text:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "x = 10\ntext = str(x)\nprint(type(text))    # &lt;class 'str'&gt;"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "x = 10\ntext = str(x)\nprint(type(text))"
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "‚≠ê <strong>Tip:</strong><br><code class=\"language-python\">input()</code> always returns a string, so sometimes you will need to convert it to <code class=\"language-python\">int</code> or <code class=\"language-python\">float</code>."
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Complete Examples"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "Example 1: User Information"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "name = \"Python\"\nage = 33\nheight = 1.74\nis_adult = True\n\nprint(\"Name:\", name)\nprint(\"Age:\", age)\nprint(\"Height:\", height)\nprint(\"Adult:\", is_adult)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Output:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "Name: Python\nAge: 33\nHeight: 1.74\nAdult: True"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "name = \"Python\"\nage = 33\nheight = 1.74\nis_adult = True\n\nprint(\"Name:\", name)\nprint(\"Age:\", age)\nprint(\"Height:\", height)\nprint(\"Adult:\", is_adult)"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle2",
      "text": "Example 2: Type Conversion"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "number = \"15\"\nnumber = int(number)\nprint(\"Sum:\", number + 5)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Output:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "Sum: 20"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "number = \"15\"\nnumber = int(number)\nprint(\"Sum:\", number + 5)"
    },
    {
      "type": "subtitle1",
      "text": "Common Errors"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "‚ùå Error when converting non-numeric text:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "int(\"hello\")\n# ValueError"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try Error >>",
      "code": "int(\"hello\")"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "‚ùå Mixing incompatible types:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "print(\"Age: \" + 20)\n# TypeError"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try Error >>",
      "code": "print(\"Age: \" + 20)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solution:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "print(\"Age:\", 20)\n# or\nprint(\"Age: \" + str(20))"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Output:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "Age: 20\nAge: 20"
    },
    {
      "type": "test-button",
      "text": "Try >>",
      "code": "print(\"Age:\", 20)\n# or\nprint(\"Age: \" + str(20))"
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "üìå <strong>Note:</strong><br>This type of error is very common when starting out. Don‚Äôt worry, you will learn to avoid them with practice."
    },
    {
